6.11	Abdullah_ibn_Salam	Abdullah, son of Salam	Abdullah ibn Salam , known also as Al-Husayn ibn Salam or Saint Abdullah ibn Salam (Arabic: â€Ž), was a companion of the prophet Muhammad, said to have been a rabbi of aristocratic stock before converting to Islam. He is credited with a large corpus of Judaic traditions Isra'iliyat, many of which are to be found in al-Tabari's (d.923) commentary on the Qur'an. He participated in the conquest of Syria and Palestine, but died in Medina.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Allah-eser-green.png/180px-Allah-eser-green.png
